This software accompanies and is fully described in the paper:
	"Samurai Survival Statistics: A Monte-Carlo Approach to Game-Theoretical Sudden Death Interactions" 
available online here: https://www.preprints.org/manuscript/202211.0419/v1

To compile software on a Linux system:
	gcc -o <output executable name> <source>.c -lgsl -lgslcblas -lm 

The GNU Scientific Library must be installed on the system.

"upper_lower.c" implements two-sided truncated distribution
"lower.c" implements one-sided trancation
